      "side": 1,
      "message": "I hope it is :-)\n\nBasically, we want to see if the distance from p1 to the line is less than the distance from p1 to the far corner of the box, along that same normal vector. The far corner being p1 + sign(n) * tolerance:\n\n  dot(p1 - p0, n) \u003c dot(sign(n) * tolerance, n)\n\nWhich reduces to:\n\n  dot(p1 - p0, n) \u003c (n.x * sign(n.x) + n.y * sign(n.y)) * tolerance\n\n  dot(p1 - p0, n) \u003c (abs(n.x) + abs(n.y)) * tolerance",
